#### Assignments
**1. Download R and RStudio:**
You will first need to download R and then RStudio.  To download R go to [this link](https://cran.rstudio.com/) and download R.  You will see links for Mac and Windows users (*see screenshot below*).  Make sure to select the appropriate one for your computer.  Download the program and then install it.

![](C:/Users/stahlm/Documents/Teaching_UnionCollege/Environmental_Data_Analysis/stahlm.github.io/ENS_215/Winter_2026/Images/RDownload_screenshot.png){width=1000px}

<br/> 

Once you've downloaded and installed R, then you will need to get RStudio.  Go to [this link](https://posit.co/download/rstudio-desktop/) scroll down a bit and then you will see links for Mac and Windows users (*see screenshot below*).  Make sure to select the appropriate one for your computer.  Download and install the software.

![](C:/Users/stahlm/Documents/Teaching_UnionCollege/Environmental_Data_Analysis/stahlm.github.io/ENS_215/Winter_2026/Images/RStudioDownload_screenshot.png){width=1000px}

